<HL>
   International Brief -- Lloyds Bank PLC:
   Six-Month Pretax Earnings
   Rose Sharply From '89 Pace
</HL>
<DATE>
07/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.LLO
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lloyds Bank PLC posted first-half pretax profit of #408
million ($740 million), nearly five times that of the
year-earlier period, when profit was curbed by extensive
Third World loan provisions.
   Pretax profit for first half of 1989 was #93 million,
largely reflecting the British bank's #483 million charge to
cover loans to less developed countries.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the latest half, Lloyds reduced such charges to #66
million. The latest charges, the bank said, were used to
cover unpaid interest on loans, primarily to Brazil and
Argentina.
