<HL>
   West German Wholesale Sales
</HL>
<DATE>
07/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   FRANKFURT, West Germany -- Sales of West German
wholesalers in June declined a real, or price-adjusted, 4%
from a year earlier and 5% in nominal or unadjusted terms,
the Federal Statistics Office said.
   June wholesale sales were valued at 73 billion marks
($44.9 billion). The agency didn't supply comparable
year-earlier figures. The monthly decline was viewed as
surprising because wholesale sales were expected to be buoyed
by the July 1 monetary and economic union of the two
Germanys.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the first half, wholesale sales rose 2% in both nominal
and adjusted terms to 437 billion marks, the statistics
office said.
