investment, indicating that he may purchase more shares as an
investment.
   Coast Savings, Los Angeles, is one of several large West
Coast thrifts that has had big losses lately from
deteriorating real estate markets. The company had a loss of
$28.7 million, or $1.89 a share, in the second quarter.
   Neither Coast Savings nor Mr. Kruttschnitt could be
reached to comment.
